South Africa remains on an adjusted lockdown level 3. President Cyril Ramaphosa made the announcement on Monday. #eNCA's Silindelo Masikane has the details. JOHANNESBURG - The health department says South Africa has recorded 15,046 new COVID-19 cases, taking the cumulative number of infections to 1,246,643. According to the department, 973, 265 recoveries have been recorded. READ: KZN has enough beds in public hospitals: Health HoD A further 416 COVID-19 related deaths are confirmed, taking the death toll to 33,579. President Cyril Ramaphosa spoke on Monday on the government's response to the coronavirus pandemic. Ramaphosa said infections in Gauteng are growing exponentially and this is expected to increase as residents return from travelling during the festive period. He warned against the new variant which is more infectious than the first identified strain of the virus. The president said South Africans should avoid the three Cs: closed spaces, crowded places, and close contact with others. He warned against the new variant which is more infectious than the first identified strain of the virus. #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 11 January .
